# meta-qing Layer

TCP Echo Server recipe for Yocto/OpenEmbedded builds.

## Layer Dependencies

- `core` (OE-Core)

## Quick Start

Add the layer to your build:

```bash
bitbake-layers add-layer meta-qing
```

## Installing TCP Echo Server

To include the TCP Echo Server in your image:

```bash
echo 'IMAGE_INSTALL:append = " tcp-echo-server"' >> conf/local.conf
```

Or in your custom image recipe:

```bash
IMAGE_INSTALL += "tcp-echo-server"
```

## Services

The TCP Echo Server includes a systemd service unit (`tcp-echo-server.service`) that is automatically enabled on boot.

To start the service:

```bash
systemctl start tcp-echo-server
```

To check status:

```bash
systemctl status tcp-echo-server
```

